snippet.textDisplay:
This fight proved that Wilder really wasn't all that great at boxing as it seemed. He was just someone who was a very big hitter. And by being that, it helped him win some fights that he could've easily lost. His 2 fights against Ortiz springs to mind.


Fury exposed how average Wilder's boxing skills are over the 2 fights. And Fury was robbed of a win in that first fight as well. Although anybody with half a brain and knowledge of boxing knows it will always be Fury 2 - 0 Wilder.
